      "is_answer_order_important": false,
      "stimulus_html": "",
      "stem_html": "Taking the relative reactivities of 1°, 2°, and 3° hydrogen atoms into account, what product(s) would you expect to obtain from monochlorination of 2-methylbutane? What would the approximate percentage of each product be? (Don’t forget to take into account the number of each kind of hydrogen.)",
